The paper deals with the design of secure codes for wireless channels with fading and Gaussian noise, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of multiple antennas (MIMO) is also mentioned, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the flatness factor of a lattice, which is a concept in signal processing (cs.SI) and numerical analysis (cs.NI).
